---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — sysviz">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>
    Working title: <strong>sysviz</strong> (the final name will be locked later).
    Built with Astro, MDX, and a hand-rolled animation runtime that auto-discovers any new
    visualization dropped into <code>src/anims/&lt;id&gt;/index.ts</code>.
  </p>
  <p>
    The site has two pillars:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/notes/">Notes</a> — long-form, structured deep dives on systems and algorithms.</li>
    <li><a href="/animations/">Animations</a> — filterable gallery of interactive demos.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Each animation honors <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code>, pauses when scrolled off-screen,
    and re-themes when the user toggles dark/light. Adding a new one is a single file.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
